OL,3,CBereavement cafe believes people need
OL,4,Cbetter support to 'manage our grief'
OL,6,F"I was very angry when my brother
OL,7,Fpassed away, and I hadn't dealt with
OL,8,Fthat at all. Then my son passed away
OL,9,Fand it was just packed together and I
OL,10,Fcouldn't deal with anything."
OL,12,F"I had too many emotions. Physical
OL,13,Fthings started to happen that I didn't
OL,14,Frealise was related to grief. And I
OL,15,Fbecame very isolated."
OL,17,FKaren Dutton, project manager of the
OL,18,FComfort Cafe, facilitates the session
OL,19,Fafter leading an earlier project for
OL,20,Fthe charity called Let's Talk
OL,21,FBereavement in north Cumbria.
