OL,3,CBereavement cafe believes people need
OL,4,Cbetter support to 'manage our grief'
OL,6,FKaren, who's also a registered nurse,
OL,7,Fsaid: "If we can enable people to feel
OL,8,Fconfident about talking about death,
OL,9,Fdying and grief, which we're very bad
OL,10,Fat, we need to normalise that so
OL,11,Fpeople feel comfortable and we can
OL,12,Fmanage our grief in our own
OL,13,Fcommunities, but also signpost when we
OL,14,Fget stuck."
OL,16,FBill Parkin started attending sessions
OL,17,Fnearby after he lost his wife more
OL,18,Fthan a year ago.
